/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `decision` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `decision` VALUES (1,'DEC001','Use authority FKs instead of ENUM columns','Entity tables had ENUM columns for status, severity, type. ENUMs embed meaning in the column type.','Replace all ENUM columns with INT FK columns pointing to authority tables (type, status, severity, etc.)','ENUMs violate LAW1 (One Authority, One Table) because they embed meaning in the column type instead of referencing an authority. Pattern ENU (No Enums) violates LAW1. By using FKs, every meaning is stored once in the authority and referenced everywhere.',2,45,'2026-07-02 20:53:04'),(2,'DEC002','Use join tables instead of 1:1 FK columns in report','The report table had 1:1 FK columns (error_id, problem_id, cause_id, fix_id). A report is never 1:1 — it has many errors, many fixes.','Drop 1:1 FK columns. Create join tables (report_error, report_problem, report_cause, report_fix, etc.) for every 1:N relationship.','A report is a container of relationships (LAW4). 1:1 FK columns violate LAW4 because they limit the report to one error, one fix. Join tables allow 1:N — queryable, indexable, normalizable.',2,45,'2026-07-02 20:53:04'),(3,'DEC003','Use variable-length arrays in BCL packets','BCL packets used repeated (\"id\";91) tuples inside containers. This repeated the key \"id\" for every value.','Use variable-length arrays: (91;94;97) instead of (\"id\";91)(\"id\";94)(\"id\";97). The container name provides the context.','Repeating \"id\" inside [@ERRORS] violates LAW5 (Context Gives Meaning). The container already says these are errors. The array should hold only the members. Store the meaning once (in the container name), reference it everywhere (in the array values).',278,45,'2026-07-02 20:53:04'),(4,'DEC004','Split foundation_law into law, pattern, pattern_law, decision','The foundation_law table mixed architectural truths (laws) with implementation patterns (forbidden patterns) and had no relationship between them.','Create four tables: law (architectural truths), pattern (forbidden/recommended), pattern_law (which laws each pattern violates), decision (design choice records).','Mixing laws and patterns in one table violates LAW1 (One Table, One Thing). A law is a law. A pattern is a pattern. A decision is a decision. No table carries multiple responsibilities. The pattern_law join table lets AI reason: pattern → violates → law.',144,45,'2026-07-02 20:53:04'),(5,'DEC005','Use Type not MethodType, ClassType, ErrorType','Code structure tables (Method, ComputationUnit, Class) needed type classification. Conventional design would create MethodType, ClassType, ErrorType — separate type tables for each entity.','Use Type as the column name in all entities. All Type columns reference the single type authority table. The table name (Method, Class, Error) provides the context.','LAW6: Never create a specialized version of a universal concept. MethodType, ClassType, ErrorType are all just Type. The table tells you what the row represents. Type tells you its classification. Creating specialized versions fragments vocabulary into incompatible mini-authorities and violates LAW1 (one authority, one table) and LAW5 (context comes from relationships).',144,45,'2026-07-02 21:11:44');

