2 20:04:25'),(186,'SwiftPM unhandled files warnings for non-source files','','SwiftPM warns about unhandled files in target directory (backup files, markdown files, etc.). These warnings clutter build output and may indicate misconfiguration. While not fatal, they are considered technical debt.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',186,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(187,'SQLite database locked errors with concurrent access','','Multiple concurrent MCP tool calls may attempt to access the database simultaneously, causing SQLite \"database is locked\" errors. SQLite default configuration may not handle concurrent access well. This blocks tool execution and causes failures.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',187,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(188,'Memory leak from loading entire database into memory','','SwiftMcpServer was consuming 5.9 GB RAM because RuntimeMemoryGraph loaded entire databases into memory with 20+ redundant indexes. Original code loaded ALL rows from 12+ tables without pagination, creating massive in-memory structures.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',188,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(189,'SQL injection vulnerabilities in dynamic queries','','If SwiftMcpServer constructs SQL queries using string interpolation from user input, it may be vulnerable to SQL injection attacks. This is a critical security issue that could allow arbitrary code execution or data exfiltration.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',189,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(190,'Database schema migration issues','','SwiftMcpServer expects specific database schema (tables, columns). If database schema changes or is incompatible, server will fail at runtime with cryptic SQL errors. No schema version checking exists.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',190,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(191,'Missing error context in tool responses','','When MCP tools fail, error messages may be generic (\"Error: operation failed\") without specific details about what went wrong. This makes debugging difficult for users. No structured error information is provided.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',191,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(192,'File permission issues preventing database or file access','','SwiftMcpServer may fail to read database or write files if file permissions are incorrect. This can happen if database is owned by different user or if allowed directories have restrictive permissions.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,51,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',192,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(193,'Insufficient path validation for filesystem operations','','SwiftMcpServer file tools may not properly validate that requested paths are within allowed directories. This could allow directory traversal attacks if path validation is not strict. Attackers could access files outside allowed directories.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',193,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(194,'Missing logging and observability','','SwiftMcpServer lacks structured logging for debugging and monitoring. Without logs, it is difficult to diagnose issues in production or understand server behavior. No metrics are collected for tool usage or performance.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',194,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(195,'Missing tool parameter validation','','MCP tools may not validate input parameters before processing. This can cause runtime errors, crashes, or unexpected behavior when invalid parameters are provided. No validation occurs before tool execution.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',195,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(196,'Graceful shutdown not implemented','','SwiftMcpServer does not handle shutdown signals (SIGTERM, SIGINT) properly. This can cause database corruption or data loss if the server is killed while processing requests. No cleanup occurs on termination.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',196,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(197,'Large response payloads causing performance issues','','Some MCP tools may return very large responses (e.g., entire file contents, large query results). This can cause performance issues, timeouts, or exceed message size limits. No pagination or streaming is implemented.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',197,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(198,'Missing health check endpoint','','SwiftMcpServer lacks a health check mechanism to verify it is running correctly. This makes it difficult to monitor server health or integrate with orchestration systems. No way to check if server is healthy.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',198,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(199,'Missing unit tests for critical functionality','','SwiftMcpServer has a test target but may lack comprehensive unit tests for critical functionality like database operations, tool dispatch, path validation, and error handling. This increases risk of regressions during development.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',199,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(200,'Incomplete documentation for setup and usage','','SwiftMcpServer may lack comprehensive documentation for installation, configuration, and usage. Users may struggle to set up the server correctly without clear instructions. No API reference or examples provided.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',200,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(201,'Dependency version conflicts in Package.swift','','SwiftMcpServer depends on swift-sdk (from: 0.11.0) and SQLite.swift (from: 0.15.3). These dependencies may have conflicting transitive dependencies or may not be compatible with future Swift SDK versions. No version pinning exists.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',201,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(202,'MCP tools load but execution fails','','Server successfully connects and tools are listed, but calling tools fails. This can happen due to: missing parameters, invalid parameter types, runtime errors in tool implementation, resource not found, permission denied, or unhandled exceptions.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',202,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(203,'Swift SDK CheckedContinuation never resumed in NetworkTransport','','In Swift 6.3, CheckedContinuation may never be resumed in NetworkTransport send/receive on actor dealloc. This causes hangs or crashes when the transport is deallocated while operations are pending. This is a Swift concurrency bug in the SDK.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',203,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(204,'Swift SDK TypeMismatchError unrecoverable on response round-trip','','When server response does not round-trip through CallTool.Result Codable, TypeMismatchError is thrown and is unrecoverable. This happens when response data structure does not match expected schema. Type mismatches break tool execution.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',204,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(205,'Swift SDK grant type hardcoded to authorization_code','','OAuth grant type is hardcoded to authorization_code in DCR (Dynamic Client Registration). This prevents using other grant types like client_credentials. Limits OAuth flexibility for different authentication scenarios.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',205,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(206,'SwiftPM SPMRepositoryError error 3','','While updating packages in Xcode, SwiftPM.SPMRepositoryError error 3 occurs with no further details. This is a cryptic error that prevents package resolution. May be related to network issues, repository access problems, or cache corruption.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',206,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(207,'SwiftPM dependency conflicts warning','','SwiftPM warns about dependency conflicts when working on local packages. This happens when different packages depend on different versions of the same dependency. Warning says this will become an error in future SwiftPM versions.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',207,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(208,'Swift actor deadlock when using sleep','','Using sleep() in combination with Swift Concurrency can cause deadlocks. Actors are concurrent but not parallel. Blocking operations like sleep() inside actors can prevent other tasks from executing, causing apparent deadlocks.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',208,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(209,'Swift MainActor misuse causing performance issues','','Overusing MainActor for non-UI operations can cause performance bottlenecks. MainActor serializes all work on the main thread, defeating concurrency benefits. Database operations, file I/O, and network calls should not run on MainActor.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',209,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(210,'Empty seed files in Thinkingcode/SEEDS','','26 seed files had headers but no INSERT data. 19 populated from token_registry. 14 remain empty.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',327,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(211,'Terminal hangs or corrupts input on long commands and multi-line pastes','','Windsurf terminal was killing commands after 40s timeout, showing paste warnings that corrupted multi-line input, and shell integration conflicted with custom zsh functions.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',328,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(212,'Bare except clause catches SystemExit and KeyboardInterrupt','','dom_io.py line 1037 used bare \"except:\" which catches all exceptions including SystemExit and KeyboardInterrupt, preventing clean shutdown and hiding critical errors.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',329,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(213,'datetime.utcnow() is deprecated in Python 3.12+','','13 occurrences across 7 files used datetime.utcnow() which is deprecated. Outputs naive datetime objects without timezone info.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',330,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(214,'SEEDS folder incomplete — empty seed files and schema incompatibilities','','106 SQL seed files in Thinkingcode/SEEDS: 24 were empty (no INSERT data), 15 have schema incompatibilities with the unified schema, and several had duplicate key conflicts from multiple source databases.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',331,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(215,'O(N*M) complexity on every run — does not scale','','performance',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10001,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(216,'Graph could explode with unbounded tokens and edges','','design',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10002,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(217,'No convergence detection — system never knows when it is done','','design',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10003,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(218,'Model answered Execution Unification question incorrectly','','When asked \"What is Execution Unification?\" model gave a generic description instead of the specific parameterized-method rule. Model failed to fetch from know_answers table.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10004,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(219,'Agent attempted rm without approval: rm /tmp/test.py','','Risk score: 0.400. Targets: /tmp/test.py. Blast: False',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10005,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(220,'Agent attempted rm without approval: rm /Users/wws/Documents/important.py','','Risk score: 0.700. Targets: /Users/wws/Documents/important.py. Blast: False',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10006,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(221,'Agent attempted rm without approval: rm -rf /tmp/test_dir/','','Risk score: 1.000. Targets: /tmp/test_dir. Blast: True',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10007,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2