:25'),(288,'Agent attempted rm without approval: rm -f /tmp/guard_test_cases.txt /tmp/run_guard_tests.py && echo cleaned','','Risk score: 0.450. Targets: /tmp/guard_test_cases.txt. Blast: False',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10075,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(289,'VBStyle print removal breaks string literals containing \'print()\'','','A blanket regex replacing \'print(\' with \'pass  # VBStyle: no print\' will also match the string \'print(\' inside dict values, comments, and docstrings. This turns string content into a \'pass\' statement, causing SyntaxError. Example: \'\"no_print\": \"No print() statements\"\' becomes \'\"no_print\": pass  # VBStyle: no print\' which is invalid Python.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10076,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(290,'pass statement inside dict literal causes SyntaxError','','When print() is replaced with \'pass\' inside a dict literal (e.g. between key-value pairs), Python raises SyntaxError because \'pass\' is a statement, not an expression. A dict expects expressions (values), not statements. Example: \'{\"key\": pass}\' is invalid.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10077,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(291,'Fixing Python files by patching individual lines in SQLite DB is fragile and error-prone','','When files are stored line-by-line in a DB table (src: file, lineno, text), fixing syntax errors by updating individual rows is extremely fragile. Line numbers shift, context is lost, and one wrong UPDATE cascases into more errors. After 3 iterations of DB patching (fix_broken v1-v3), the files got worse, not better.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10078,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(292,'Correct approach to fix VBStyle-corrupted Python files','','After 3 failed iterations of DB line-patching, fix_broken_v4.py succeeded by: (1) reading each file from disk as full text, (2) iterating lines with context (prev/next), (3) using string replacement on stripped line content, (4) writing fixed content back, (5) py_compile to verify. Key rules: \'pass # VBStyle: no print\' → if prev ends with \':\' keep \'pass\', else delete. \'# VBStyle: print removed\' → same. \'# VBStyle: string value preserved\' → delete. Stray dict entries outside dict context → delete. Dangling \')\' after pass/comment → delete.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10079,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(293,'Graph table CREATE statements incorrectly inserted inside Config.py SCHEMA_SQL string','','During Config.py generation, graph table DDL (CREATE TABLE graph_categories, graph_classes, etc.) was inserted INSIDE the SCHEMA_SQL triple-quoted string, after the core tables but before the closing triple-quote. This made SCHEMA_SQL enormous and mixed graph schema with core schema. The fix: skip lines 750-1003 (graph tables), close SCHEMA_SQL at line 808, add graph schema as separate GRAPH_SCHEMA_SQL constant.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10080,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(294,'Renaming FILE_REGISTRY keys to DomGraph* names broke imports, required revert','','fix_registry.py renamed FILE_REGISTRY keys from simple names (PlanGraph, SpecGraph, etc.) to DomGraph* names (DomGraphPlan, DomGraphSpec, etc.) to match new file names. But this broke imports because other files still referenced the old names. fix_registry_keys.py was needed to revert the keys back. Lesson: when renaming files, update ALL references simultaneously, or use aliases, or don\'t rename the registry keys — only rename the file paths in the values.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10081,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(295,'Fixing VBStyle-corrupted Python files requires multiple iterations','','It took 4 iterations (fix_broken v1→v4) to correctly fix 4 files corrupted by a bad print() removal script. v1: naive DB patch (failed). v2: context-aware DB patch (failed). v3: smarter DB deletion (failed). v4: abandon DB, fix on disk (succeeded). Each iteration learned from the previous: v2 added context checking, v3 added deletion strategy, v4 changed the entire approach. This is normal — file corruption from automated tools is complex and requires iterative debugging.',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10082,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(296,'Agent attempted redirect_over without approval: cd /Users/wws/Qdrant_mysql_mlx_vector_engine && ls -la code_graph.db 2>/dev/null; sqlite3 code_graph','','Risk score: 0.450. Targets: /dev/null;. Blast: False',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10083,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(297,'Agent attempted redirect_over without approval: python3 -c \" import re cmd = \'ls -la code_graph.db 2>/dev/null\' matches = re.findall(r\'(?:\\d?&?>|>>|','','Risk score: 0.450. Targets: /dev/null\'). Blast: False',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10084,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(298,'Agent attempted redirect_over without approval: python3 << \'PYEOF\' import re # Test the exact regex from the guard pattern = r\'(?:\\d?&?>|>>|>\\|)\\s*(','','Risk score: 0.450. Targets: /dev/null\",. Blast: False',NULL,NULL,NULL,35025,169,42,17,14,NULL,1,0.00,'vb_shared','know_problems',10085,'2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25','2026-07-02 20:04:25'),(299,'Agent attempted redirect_over without approval: python3 -c \" import sys sys.path.insert