answer first?','f1aa0b772530ab711d678183ac32c185',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2420,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2402,'A] Root Questions (Domain \\u2192 Operation \\u2192 Strictness)\\n# [ ] Any questions in any order\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule if the user is unsure?','66c7ffab717f8af5b34e8e831fd40107',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2421,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2403,'Question | Yes | No | Other |\\n|---|---:|---:|---|\\n| Are you asking \\u201chow many GUI-domain questions should exist in the Q/A registry\\u201d (a target count)?','bf475c1e1047fa10db9a8da7d6265116',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2422,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2404,'Do you want a fixed numeric answer (not \\u201cit depends\\u201d)?','9f1586a9d1afa348c24d53a33487bc10',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2423,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2405,'MAXED ROOT Q/A \\u2014 \\u201cHow to Answer\\u201d Protocol (Q/A Registry Control Layer)\\n\\n# Q: What is the user expected to do in this Q/A registry?','e6a537362baebf9153f9933a0ff4bfbb',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2424,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2406,'A] Check only the acceptable options; everything unchecked is excluded\\n# [ ] Write explanations in free text\\n# [ ] Answer everything every time\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the required answering order?','dbf8f01dbac716bc21119b9d99a7378f',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2425,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2407,'A] Root questions first, then only the required subtree questions\\n# [ ] Any order is allowed\\n# [ ] File order only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is Root 1 (the first gating root)?','2376d81b61a9331ad272ad889e82cf60',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2426,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2408,'A] Domain selection\\n# [ ] Operation selection\\n# [ ] Strictness selection\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is Root 2 (the second gating root)?','15b351f8aeb5d36f1577e87ba3341baa',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2427,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2409,'A] Operation selection\\n# [ ] Domain selection\\n# [ ] Strictness selection\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is Root 3 (the third gating root)?','bb39b6083403bc60c14f514ea4faa1de',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2428,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2410,'A] Strictness selection\\n# [ ] Domain selection\\n# [ ] Operation selection\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must Root 1 be exactly one selection (single-select)?','12e419b550c276e857dcdf59acaed6b1',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2429,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2411,'A] Yes, exactly one option must be checked\\n# [ ] No, multiple domains can be checked\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must Root 2 be exactly one selection (single-select)?','1c9cb128eeb163297088036233d2a7e7',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2430,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2412,'A] Yes, exactly one option must be checked\\n# [ ] No, multiple operations can be checked\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must Root 3 be exactly one selection (single-select)?','f02f4c0fd2c844193bea8c21e5c12544',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2431,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2413,'A] Yes, exactly one option must be checked\\n# [ ] No, multiple strictness modes can be checked\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: How are questions classified for selection (required vs optional)?','8268b0f9dc2483268a54e75ebedbf4c5',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2432,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2414,'A] Each question declares REQUIRES: <operation list>; if current operation matches, question is required\\n# [ ] All questions are always required\\n# [ ] Requiredness is inferred automatically (no tags)\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Is a question allowed to have zero checked options?','26c836405c56f44f130919c09bc9db96',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2433,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2415,'A] Yes, but only if it is not required for the current operation\\n# [ ] No, every question must have at least one checked option always\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if a required question has zero checked options?','359193ce9419a25139633820f5819696',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2434,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2416,'A] Validation fails (no guessing allowed)\\n# [ ] Default to [S] options\\n# [ ] Treat as allow-all\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Are multiple options allowed to be checked on non-root questions?','498253c6ac466ad68046dd6cc6c64c17',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2435,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2417,'A] Yes, if the question is explicitly marked MULTI_SELECT:true\\n# [ ] No, single-select only everywhere\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If MULTI_SELECT:true and multiple options are checked, what does it mean?','fb59a8f8286cb2c9741991037d6daf55',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2436,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2418,'A] Allowed set is the union of checked options\\n# [ ] Allowed set is the intersection of checked options\\n# [ ] Multi-check is always an error\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If MULTI_SELECT:false and multiple options are checked, what happens?','0c5b77a7423eaf54f908c12748936064',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2437,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2419,'A] Validation fails\\n# [ ] Left-to-right wins\\n# [ ] Latest edit wins\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Are \\u201cOther:\\u201d free-text options executable by default?','f3e900022651f2048aa425b32718f632',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2438,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2420,'A] No, \\u201cOther\\u201d is inert unless explicitly checked AND given a deterministic definition elsewhere\\n# [ ] Yes, \\u201cOther\\u201d is always allowed\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: How must \\u201cOther:\\u201d be defined to become deterministic?','f276fd11813ae2a745951026360c5ae7',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2439,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2421,'A] \\u201cOther\\u201d must be checked AND a matching definition block must exist with exact parsing rules\\n# [ ] \\u201cOther\\u201d is interpreted by the model as best effort\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the authoritative source of truth for allowed choices?','2c22de31b71bde6e6dd4ae00daee2994',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2440,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2422,'A] Q/A registry selections + Constitution invariants; conflicts are errors\\n# [ ] Q/A registry only\\n# [ ] Constitution text only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if the Q/A registry conflicts with the Constitution invariants?','32f3c0639fcb43a59276fa937291767e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2441,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2423,'A] Validation fails until reconciled\\n# [ ] Q/A overrides Constitution\\n# [ ] Constitution overrides Q/A automatically\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Are unselected options considered \\u201cunknown\\u201d or \\u201cforbidden\\u201d?','0b99ba9aeab1dbbb2e6c316e86da8d6b',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2442,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2424,'A] Forbidden (excluded)\\n# [ ] Unknown (can be chosen later without change)\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Is the model allowed to propose or select an unchecked option during execution?','dfb65bbc7004e9001922f751028d7361',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2443,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2425,'A] No, unchecked is forbidden\\n# [ ] Yes, suggestions are allowed but not execution\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: When suggestions are allowed, how must they be emitted?','973a4488b1c3285a2bd4d7b4625ed3b1',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2444,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2426,'A] Suggestions must be output as new unchecked options only (no behavior change until checked)\\n# [ ] Suggestions can be applied automatically\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the required output of a compliance check?','9b6e370a4db257e8a6e429411a21e7be',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2445,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2427,'A] Pass/Fail + deterministic diff list (expected vs found) + fix directives\\n# [ ] Pass/Fail only\\n# [ ] Narrative explanation\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the required behavior on Fail?','de70bbeee691834f17f657f09111cb46',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2446,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2428,'A] Stop (no partial, no continue)\\n# [ ] Continue with best effort\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must every run record a report packet to the ledger?','2d3b4c9cbce4720efc31dfbca3215b12',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2447,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2429,'A] Yes, always append-only\\n# [ ] Optional\\n# [ ] No\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the minimum content of every report packet?','aa5139f0a547995d9f24f0ee0848a5af',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2448,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2430,'A] emitter class name + input parameters + output tuple + errors\\n# [ ] output only\\n# [ ] errors only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must the registry be machine-parseable with strict formatting rules?','d75b616480c96c973240bff16b13c7e5',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2449,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2431,'A] Yes, strict markers required (# Q:, option lines start with # [)\\n# [ ] No, free-form is acceptable\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must section ordering be explicit?','452a17def91316f3ca44126c08a00139',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2450,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2432,'A] Yes, SECTION and SECTION_ORDER required\\n# [ ] No, file order only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must question identifiers exist (QID/QKEY)?','ed206b44fb69b48efa902413a8af8304',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2451,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2433,'A] Yes, both QID (order-based) and QKEY (stable) are required\\n# [ ] QID only\\n# [ ] QKEY only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Is QID allowed to change after re-index?','2b044cea467043acc088d9a3078d072e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2452,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2434,'A] Yes, QID may renumber; QKEY is the stable reference\\n# [ ] No, QID never changes\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if duplicate QKEYs exist?','81b0eeeaf6497ed1ccc4c520881d00b2',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2453,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2435,'A] Validation fails (questions must be unique)\\n# [ ] Allow duplicates\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: How does the system decide which subtree questions to ask?','fd2e246339b1ba3712c8d9ac1c4a4e3d',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2454,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2436,'Q: Must the AI translate the human request into an explicit Operation Plan before doing anything?','e3ab6ce53f8e63f17509752d938ad912',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2455,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2437,'A] Yes, AI must produce an Operation Plan first\\n# [ ] No, AI can execute directly\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is an Operation Plan?','572245e3e7580252c52bf075907d51f2',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2456,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2438,'A] A list of Items, each Item has: domain, operation, target, required questions, execution steps\\n# [ ] A single sentence summary\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Can a single human request contain multiple Items?','df9bd119d744ec1ffbd6849fac2d41cb',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2457,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2439,'A] Yes, multi-item requests are allowed\\n# [ ] No, one request must map to one item only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If multiple Items exist, what is the execution rule?','fbcbdbc9dce8b0d71813b765eff0f0a9',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2458,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2440,'A] Execute items sequentially in plan order; any failure stops the whole run\\n# [ ] Execute items independently; failures don\\u2019t stop others\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: How does the AI detect multiple Items in one request?','920d5baed2327d4e7a467bd45d526eb6',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2459,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2441,'A] Split by explicit targets (multiple segments/files/commands) and by conjunctions (\\u201cand\\u201d, \\u201calso\\u201d, lists)\\n# [ ] Never split; treat as one item\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if the AI cannot map part of the request to a known domain or operation?','127e2537cbaa2c2201b47bbbf0c8a9de',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2460,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2442,'A] Fail with \\u201cunmapped item\\u201d (no guessing)\\n# [ ] Default to GUI domain\\n# [ ] Default to Validate operation\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for selecting the Domain from a human request?','4f469cc62765116e7b9476b25e1b62e5',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2461,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2443,'A] Use explicit keywords; if ambiguous, fail (no guessing)\\n# [ ] Use best guess\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for selecting the Operation from a human request?','8efa2a4a6358352e405ff2064498b9d1',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2462,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2444,'A] Use explicit verbs (generate/validate/sync/run/extract); if missing, fail\\n# [ ] Default to Validate\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Are different Items allowed to use different Domains in the same request?','0bdf28c52299ffe6459612fcb4491cd2',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2463,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2445,'A] Yes, each Item can have its own domain\\n# [ ] No, all items must share one domain\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Are different Items allowed to use different Operations in the same request?','e011968b4f9739c325c1d24aa4b5a992',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2464,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2446,'A] Yes, each Item can have its own operation\\n# [ ] No, all items must share one operation\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the \\u201cRequired Questions\\u201d selection mechanism?','c37352b6fea2fdcfe8a198b3fbed896e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2465,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2447,'A] Each question declares REQUIRES tags; required set = all questions whose REQUIRES matches the Item\\u2019s operation and domain\\n# [ ] Required set is \\u201ceverything\\u201d\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If a required question is unanswered (no checked options), what happens?','470271a61d570a438dd8983665d6bbfa',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2466,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2448,'A] Fail the Item (no guessing)\\n# [ ] Use suggested defaults\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If a question is multi-select and multiple options are checked, what does that mean?','69d21ee5c2414e97461182bfb84a5b9a',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2467,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2449,'A] Allowed set is the union of checked options\\n# [ ] Intersection only\\n# [ ] Error\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for \\u201cOther:\\u201d options in relation to human requests?','22d715bb1897ae82118bad3b89c0d5b2',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2468,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2450,'A] \\u201cOther\\u201d is ignored unless checked AND defined deterministically in a separate definition block\\n# [ ] \\u201cOther\\u201d may be interpreted as best-effort\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must the AI produce a \\u201cRequest\\u2192Plan\\u2192Questions\\u201d trace in the report packet?','427650a1f98ae3d37515d44855e28dcc',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2469,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2451,'A] Yes, required (so you can audit why it asked what it asked)\\n# [ ] Optional\\n# [ ] No\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What must each Item contain (minimum fields)?','d5e4872db00a2e078672b0d93849bf10',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2470,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2452,'A] item_id, domain, operation, targets, required_questions, selected_answers, pass_fail, diff, fix_directives\\n# [ ] Only domain and operation\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: How are targets represented for multi-item requests?','b0420305e14499fbdd3bfd1c843e1644',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2471,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2453,'No, one target per Item only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the failure policy when one target in a multi-target Item fails?','cac8f410ae64a2380024e186b9df1a1c',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2472,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2454,'A] Fail the Item and stop remaining targets\\n# [ ] Continue remaining targets\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must the AI re-check compliance before each target is executed?','1c9534fe590735effecbe8f80d914c63',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2473,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2455,'ROOT_QUESTIONS_BLOCK_TO_CREATE_FIRST]\\n# Q: What is the current domain being evaluated?','f5ac0573bcc26c0d3c08f4a89e55f831',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2474,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2456,'GUI (PyQt6)\\n# [ ] Python (Backend / Codegen)\\n# [ ] Swift\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the current operation?','d5539cf4b5ce833260f730ad18683164',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2475,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2457,'Generate\\n# [ ] Validate\\n# [ ] Sync\\n# [ ] Run\\n# [ ] Extract-Index\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the strictness level?','3a7795fd066c265e4eb4bca36326da37',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2476,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2458,'What I need from you (only 2 decisions)\\n1) For missing required answers: do you want **Fail** or **Discovery Branch** as default?','f881992fafa587134ba6ae8991e1b132',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2477,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2459,'What would Wayne do (with *this* \\u201cno guessing \\u2192 discovery\\u201d topic)?','7988f635b75af627a67be6cc931a1a6e',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2478,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2460,'If you want it as a literal Q/A root block (drop-in):\\n\\n# Q: If a required answer is missing, what would Wayne do?','7d40f733a229511af0308f8c6ddcf5a9',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2479,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2461,'FINAL_STATE_TODAY]\\n- A real \\u201cVBSTYLE cognition loop\\u201d run exists:\\n  - ingest \\u201cwhat we have\\u201d into DB\\n  - derive missing questions/placeholders from DB state\\n  - enforce no-guess gates\\n  - produce a ledger entry showing: inputs \\u2192 derived questions \\u2192 answers status \\u2192 next actions\\n\\n[START_POINT_REQUIRED]\\n- \\u201cWhat do we have?','88b72c5dd9f970f350d373ce1ec5c529',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2480,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2462,'If bracket headers inconsistent \\u2192 derive question: \\u201cWhat is the header sentinel format?','f71376ffaa97a26f6aca2632314abb42',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2481,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2463,'If no generator script found \\u2192 derive question: \\u201cWhich script is authoritative for generate/validate?','f77645a3bd6682e454780013c148f3c5',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1