 GitHub repo task?','2866e229fadd8406e6729001a27e71d5',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2559,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2541,'W] No, web search is secondary; local repo evidence is primary\\n# [ ] Yes, web search first\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the web search used for in GitHub tasks?','a7fee4e1d05663091e45dd05bcb28a03',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2560,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2542,'W] Only to verify external facts not present in repo (dependencies/docs), after local scan\\n# [ ] For general guessing/interpretation\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the stop rule if repo evidence is insufficient?','d12e4e1092b69c03357dbcd9cb960f45',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2561,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2543,'VB-Style GUI Segment System \\u2014 Additional Q/A Blocks (same format)\\n\\n# Q: What is the authoritative source for events?','24f65f0ee8c7c95dbc28161eb1448036',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2562,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2544,'Bracket-only: events must appear only inside bracket_dom\\n# [ ] YAML-only: events must appear only in YAML events: mapping\\n# [ ] Both allowed, YAML overrides brackets on conflict\\n# [ ] Both allowed, brackets override YAML on conflict\\n# [ ] Both allowed, merge union; conflicts are errors\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the authoritative source for dependencies?','162d7be7bfc73c8e212b75a16cbdf3da',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2563,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2545,'YAML-only dependencies list is authoritative\\n# [ ] Bracket-only (dependencies encoded in bracket_dom) is authoritative\\n# [ ] Both allowed, YAML overrides brackets on conflict\\n# [ ] Both allowed, merge union; conflicts are errors\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the required bracket header boundary in each file?','649a6370159dd8f8ea9705b2957326cf',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2564,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2546,'Must be the first triple-quote block in the file\\n# [ ] Must start with a fixed marker line: \"Bracket DOM:\"\\n# [ ] Must start/end with fixed sentinel lines: \"[BRACKET_DOM_START]\" / \"[BRACKET_DOM_END]\"\\n# [ ] Must be a YAML front-matter block at top of file\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the formal bracket grammar rule for properties?','b7872b5f297a37507b6131d6bd8a116e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,1,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2565,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2547,'Both allowed (colon and equals treated the same)\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for quoting string values in brackets?','cbe2283fa86545bafe13ad83defd6d43',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2566,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2548,'Double quotes required for strings\\n# [ ] Single quotes required for strings\\n# [ ] Quotes optional when no spaces/special chars; otherwise required\\n# [ ] Always treat unquoted tokens as strings unless typed otherwise\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for escaping inside quoted strings?','a307143464e19b79380b497042ea607c',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2567,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2549,'Backslash escaping (\\\\n, \\\\\", \\\\\\\\)\\n# [ ] No escapes allowed; reject if special characters present\\n# [ ] JSON-style escaping only\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for commas and whitespace inside brackets?','ce446d25bd8cdabd931f45f8a51d2083',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,1,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2568,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2550,'Commas required between all items\\n# [ ] Commas