 generator outputs minimal formatting only\\n# [ ] Optional via config flag\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Should verification validate against live PyQt6 introspection (import widget class and check hasattr/setter)?','443a44bc2f3070c033fdc508bbcccc23',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2605,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2587,'Yes, use runtime introspection\\n# [ ] No, use static mapping tables only\\n# [ ] Both; mismatch is error\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Should bracket parsing allow arbitrary Python expressions as values?','dad72fbfcbcfb333479c46036d27cf57',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2606,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2588,'Okay, so for the domain of GUI, you could have an amount of questions there, right?','f44d0fd386f3ff8f321dc333a24c42b9',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2607,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2589,'How many questions do you think you could have for GUI?','274057198b03b17467b142b4a085822f',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2608,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2590,'STATE_CAPTURE]\\n- \\u201cWhat do I have?','c14eb5b7f8778d52fcba43cd1147e6eb',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2609,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2591,'What is already working?','0cb8aaeee2ecd69bde48cf68a0ea8815',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2610,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2592,'What is forbidden?','fad92c3f8f3831212560cb0d57d4dd53',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2611,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2593,'What is required?','df9ad5d6d95e6e9b0759cd5e795acd55',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2612,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2594,'Then the model can go look at how that is generated and reason it out, you know what I mean?','9a6065626a32c474c2a1ef12cc9e19e7',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2613,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2595,'Yes: each question becomes a branch (tree item)\\nYou can represent it as a tree where:\\n- **Question = branch node**\\n- **Each option = child node**\\n- **Checked options = allowed leaves**\\n- **Unchecked options = pruned leaves**\\n- **Other: ____ = \\u201cnew leaf to be classified\\u201d** (must be checked explicitly or rejected)\\n\\n### Example branch (decorators)\\n# Q: Are decorators allowed in GUI-domain Python code?','64d2db98fcec477665dfc911108e5756',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2614,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2596,'Yes, decorators allowed\\n# [W] No, decorators forbidden\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\nTree view (conceptual):\\n- Q(Decorators allowed?','65faa6c7f9ca319aff31f3dac8db33e0',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2615,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2597,'One rule you must add for \\u201cOther:\\u201d\\nBecause \\u201cOther\\u201d can reintroduce guessing unless locked:\\n\\n# Q: Is \\u201cOther:\\u201d allowed to be executed without being explicitly checked and defined?','8eab18adb818f891978a393e7600d705',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2616,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2598,'So what other questions, uh, can you generate as many other questions that you think can, like, I can put in here?','c4dd67499433f35b6e38a2da16e14166',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2617,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2599,'THE ROOT QUESTION THAT SELECTS THE WHOLE PLAN]\\n- \\u201cWhat is the supreme anchor: Existing working script, or DB-first always?','128c4b766cbba1f55e046ab2deedeb26',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2618,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2600,'Yes, override immediately\\n# [W] No, working path stays anchor; preference requires gated migration\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What must be proven before executing a preference migration?','1c070eb452f43161a97685f6a44f683c',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2619,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2601,'W] Migration must preserve or recreate the working path, be reversible, and pass validation gates\\n# [ ] Only preference alignment matters\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If preference and reality conflict, what is the execution order?','c43f7869d387387e422e4e204cf92992',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2620,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2602,'Is there \\u201can answer\\u201d?','b4d75d77cf1476780084f9097e432a8d',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2621,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2603,'A] Select allowed options only; unchecked options are excluded; unanswered required questions cause validation failure\\n# [ ] Provide narrative explanations in free text\\n# [ ] Answer all questions every time regardless of operation\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the step order for answering?','75d5fcb7ded60df09d054f9b695af1d8',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2622,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2604,'A] Answer root questions first (Domain \\u2192 Operation \\u2192 Strictness), then only the required subtree questions\\n# [ ] Answer questions in file order always\\n# [ ] Answer any subset arbitrarily\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if the user is unsure?','2832aa3bfa49359869beb3e7b7484ac0',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2623,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2605,'I know this is a bit out of our conversation, right?','90fd1deb0165f124730e352cde3c64d4',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2624,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2606,'But, so, for example, let\'s say I have an SVG, right, and it\'s got data system, ledger system, discovery domain, all these different SVs, right?','7ef15164c9c2013e3e86227fb3bc38ff',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2625,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2607,'And if I had a, like, if I could click on, like, domain, and then it takes it, like, you get a 3D view of going into the domain, you understand?','0d5274bb1bf8c23709de1b6d51636f34',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2626,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2608,'Could you generate that for me if I give you this?','8243f51889d3c691e12eb2f6f3309d70',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2627,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2609,'Pick only if convergence succeeds**\\n- Otherwise: **UNKNOWN**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Drop-in Q/A blocks to enforce it\\n\\n# Q: If the AI is missing required information, what must it do?','0bb2ef3861b8da81b17bcbf2be74ceaf',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2628,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2610,'W] Run Discovery Branch (local evidence \\u2192 web evidence \\u2192 convergence test \\u2192 resolve or UNKNOWN)\\n# [ ] Guess\\n# [ ] Skip the requirement\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: How many web candidates must be collected when running discovery?','85027d400ace75fca0ab0d85df626c70',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2629,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2611,'W] 10\\n# [ ] 3\\n# [ ] 20\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the rule for selecting a candidate answer?','99366e0ec445560dfa6189d2efa433f6',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2630,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2612,'W] Only select if it fits the allowed options AND converges by evidence ranking; otherwise UNKNOWN\\n# [ ] Select the most popular\\n# [ ] Select the first result\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if discovery cannot produce a single allowed answer?','0e6c81c7d56927ab16885c8e6b5d046a',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2631,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2613,'Add this as a VBSTYLE-compatible \\u201cUser Pattern\\u201d Q/A section\\n\\n# Q: Is the AI allowed to use past user patterns to expand intent?','b84386fa3fb8bd68a710fbe3b2bf4529',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2632,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2614,'A] Yes, but only via explicit Pattern Tokens defined in the Q/A registry (no implicit guessing)\\n# [ ] Yes, the AI can infer patterns implicitly\\n# [ ] No, ignore past patterns\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the allowed evidence source for pattern matching?','1eb85917498329b8cf3b3318c3df732e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2633,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2615,'A] Current request text + registered Pattern Tokens only\\n# [ ] Current request + any past chat inference\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Must the AI output the matched Pattern Tokens it used?','4167eae623e8a1500acefd4ccb8797a9',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2634,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2616,'A] Yes, required (audit)\\n# [ ] Optional\\n# [ ] No\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if the user pattern is ambiguous (matches multiple tokens)?','544296d16df3b85804ec381dae3e6cd0',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2635,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2617,'A] Fail (no guessing)\\n# [ ] Pick the highest priority token\\n# [ ] Merge all matched packets\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Can the user request include multiple Pattern Tokens intentionally?','beb015984efb0b139c8a9e7fb9dfd973',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2636,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2618,'A] Yes, merge packets by union; conflicts are errors\\n# [ ] No, only one token allowed\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Example Pattern Token (your \\u201cmax\\u201d)\\n\\n# Q: PATTERN_TOKEN: \\u201cmax\\u201d means what?','706921d7276d2bf3d114f6bffff7a5b2',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2637,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2619,'Q: Are multiple options allowed to be checked for a single question?','d6982caf1e7d2947ebad132dd4ed64aa',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2638,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2620,'No, exactly one option must be checked\\n# [ ] Yes, multiple options may be checked\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If multiple options are checked, what does it mean?','247a8e27a2d68ff1d0e42a46149dcda3',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2639,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2621,'Allowed set = union of checked options\\n# [ ] Allowed set = intersection of checked options only\\n# [ ] Multi-check is always an error\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if a required question has zero checked options?','8f92ac57fc6410f16fa8af4c48a02e6e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2640,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2622,'Error: validation fails (no guessing allowed)\\n# [ ] Treat as \\u201callow all\\u201d\\n# [ ] Treat as \\u201cdeny all\\u201d\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\nAnd one more that matters for enforcement:\\n\\n# Q: What is the authoritative source for \\u201callowed choices\\u201d during execution?','f00b09e4dd37da759beeff79a0c40da8',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2641,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2623,'INTENT EXPANSION (User Meaning \\u2192 Must-Have Packet)\\n\\n# Q: Is intent expansion allowed (short user phrases expand into full requirement sets)?','e9cd95d3bfa66c581eb507ec7ebab8fe',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2642,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2624,'A] Yes, intent expansion is allowed\\n# [ ] No, only literal requests are allowed\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is an \\u201cIntent Token\\u201d?','b8b8b0d24081497ec17995744c15f4e1',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2643,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2625,'A] A short keyword that maps to a deterministic Must-Have Packet\\n# [ ] A free-form hint the AI interprets\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: Where are Intent Tokens defined?','3f48557468eb382efa567973c261a37e',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2644,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2626,'A] In the Q/A registry under an \\u201cINTENTS\\u201d section (machine-parseable)\\n# [ ] In code comments scattered in files\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: If a user message contains an Intent Token, what happens?','f3c68456add0a7799ab25dd3f00b1d86',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2645,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2627,'A] The AI must attach the Must-Have Packet to the Operation Plan for that request\\n# [ ] The AI may optionally use it\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if multiple Intent Tokens are present?','f3fb5da7875a3156f1b5db300a890225',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2646,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2628,'A] Merge Must-Have Packets by union; conflicts are errors\\n# [ ] Merge and let the AI decide conflicts\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What happens if an Intent Token is unknown (not in INTENTS section)?','adf9de471980ccc05ede4a385f863a94',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2647,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2629,'A] Fail (no guessing)\\n# [ ] Ignore unknown token\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: What is the precedence when Intent Packet conflicts with explicit user text?','cb6ed8754694f84e2bed60366fa687d6',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2648,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2630,'A] Explicit user text overrides intent packet; conflicts must be reported\\n# [ ] Intent packet overrides user text\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n---\\n\\n# INTENTS \\u2014 PYQT6 GUI (Example)\\n\\n# Q: INTENT_TOKEN: \\u201cmake a pyqt6 gui\\u201d means what Domain and Operation?','42fe6b182448e04d83f0c52e97aa0441',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2649,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2631,'A] Domain=GUI(PyQt6) + Operation=Generate\\n# [ ] Domain=Python + Operation=Generate\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: INTENT_TOKEN: \\u201cmake a pyqt6 gui\\u201d Must-Haves include which items?','b837a53eb9e093235d913ec9e6777e34',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2650,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2632,'Maximum features allowed (union of all optional capabilities)\\n# [ ] Maximum strictness (fail on unknown, no warnings)\\n# [ ] Maximum completeness (fill in every required section)\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: INTENT_TOKEN: \\u201cmax\\u201d for GUI generation Must-Haves include which?','084a09ebe2277efe93d5471c9be5cac7',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2651,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2633,'Generated UI code structure (widgets, layouts, imports, signals)\\n- Backend code structure (handlers exist, signatures)\\n- Optional: runtime introspection (PyQt6 import + hasattr checks)\\n\\n### 3) Compliance check (the \\u201cmodel notices mistakes\\u201d part)\\nA model can detect wrongness by running these comparisons:\\n\\n- **Rule compliance**: Code violates an invariant?','56b3d9e52c92946d2acec78ea3b210dd',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2652,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2634,'Decision compliance**: Code contradicts a selected Q/A?','c5e1ad21e5fd4d43e5024287cab4dc23',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2653,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2635,'Index compliance**: File header brackets differ from central index brackets?','84729365425a4ca07cf8bad6d71543b6',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2654,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2636,'Structural compliance**: Generated UI doesn\\u2019t match parsed widget tree?','599a693ea065628fbde7210175273d05',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2655,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2637,'Event compliance**: Bracket-declared signals not connected / handlers missing?','b1fe27fabcb9ade4677a7e2a1178f18b',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2656,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2638,'Now, I don\'t know how, what am I supposed to search?','50bc8e3a020493376f60a1652c62eeb5',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2657,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2639,'What\'s the right thing to search there for?','f5a7fce856174b8499d7df93bd53bbc4',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2658,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2640,'Add this as the \\u201cNO GUESSING \\u2192 DISCOVERY\\u201d subtree (Q/A format)\\n\\n# Q: If a required answer is missing, is the AI allowed to run discovery steps to find the correct answer?','5f3a07279c4bc64e057ccc149d05d86b',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',2659,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(2641,'A] Yes, discovery is required before failing\\n# [ ] No, missing answer always fails immediately\\n# [ ] Other: _________________________\\n\\n# Q: 