'',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3905,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3886,'Is the workflow realistic?','ce7db9507cb8fa75478229cd49ddb2b9',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3906,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3887,'Where your bracket system shines vs needing a model\\n\\n### Brackets + validators can fully solve:\\n- structure compliance\\n- rule mapping completeness\\n- workflow stage coverage\\n- missing evidence emission\\n- mismatch between declared IO and ledger schema\\n- joiner syntax correctness\\n- boundary violations (cross-domain edges)\\n\\n### A model still helps for:\\n- naming quality\\n- \\u201cdoes this intention match reality?','ba65144dac10a129858bdab0ed1a8e32',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3907,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3888,'So you need explicit obligations like:\\n- Every class must declare: intention, domain, inputs, outputs, errors\\n- Every operation must have: param\\u2192validate\\u2192execute\\u2192cleanup\\n- Every execute must emit: evidence record\\n- Every rule claim must link to: implementing method(s)\\n\\n### Missing #3 \\u2014 Joiner semantics contract\\nYour model says \\u201cvalidate joiner compliance,\\u201d but **what is a valid joiner**?','3cbd23a33b99e599a256872156539402',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3908,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3889,'If You Want \\u201cJust Press Play Like Python\\u201d\\n\\nThen the fastest setup is:\\n\\n- Install **MinGW**\\n- Add gcc to PATH\\n- Use Option 2 above\\n\\nThen Windsurf behaves like Python:\\n\\u25b6\\ufe0f \\u2192 build \\u2192 run\\n\\n---\\n\\nIf you tell me:\\n- Are you using MSVC or MinGW?','763eb32740e3b80aeefe650286bae684',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3909,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3890,'Do you already have gcc working in terminal?','4f4b92f52a62484ef231f5c085183d4a',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3910,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3891,'Auth method defined per target\\n- Worker/timeouts envelope defined\\n\\n### Gate C (Charged)\\n- One end-to-end call from GUI (or curl) returns correct deterministic packet\\n\\n---\\n\\n## The one design choice that will decide if this stays clean\\n**Do you want the HTTP server to:**\\n1) run SSH **from the Mac to other machines** (Mac is the controller), or  \\n2) expose \\u201cSSH-like control\\u201d **into the Mac itself** (Mac is the target)?','669d5613367e13e796baac999da89a66',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3911,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3892,'So do I, like, do I just check my browser or what?','ecee8c43bde56d53557197a45017a300',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3912,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3893,'So is what you\'re saying about correct or what?','1b5c3567d9a68f0c3b0a8a5c4c3eeaef',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3913,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3894,'BOUNDARY-CONTROL ANALYSIS**\\r\\nApply Wayne\'s domain boundaries:\\r\\n- Each class has ONE domain - validate no cross-domain responsibilities\\r\\n- Check joiner compliance: Does `ClassName[method[parameter]]` actually match domain?','4071de32a74345820323e67f03a727bf',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3914,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3895,'COGNITIVE NETWORK VALIDATION**\\r\\nUse Wayne\'s decision graph architecture:\\r\\n- Create dependency graph of framework\\r\\n- Validate activation paths (does SSH actually use Config?','8db1c4a90875fa5c830509bd9aa5f42f',9,NULL,NULL,NULL,'chatgpt','',0,1,2,'chatgpt_export','Questions',3915,'question_text','2026-07-02 19:43:11'),(3896,'CAPABILITY GATE ANALYSIS**\\r\\nApply Wayne\'s gates to pattern validation:\\r\\n- **Torch**: Does analysis methodology exist and transferable?','d8c6708a8c012fd1faf